{"lemma":"مُفْرَد","slug":"مُفْرَد","root":"ف.ر.د","root_slug":"ف-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33452","n33453","n33455"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"singular","tags":["singular"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"A single word or its equivalent, distinct from a full sentence or a clause.","examples":[{"text":"والثالثة الواقعة خبرًا لـ \"إن\" وأخواتها كقولك: إن عمرًا قام أبوه، فقولك \"قام أبوه\" جملةٌ في موضع رفع، لأن المفرد الذي وقعت موقعه مرفوع، كأنك قلت: إن زيدًا قائم، أو قائمُ الأب؛ وهذه أيضًا لا تكون إلا مرفوعة الموضع، لا غير، لأن خبر \"إنّ\" لا يكون إلا مرفوعًا."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"simple"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of أَفْرَدَ (ʔafrada)."},"ipa":["/muf.rad/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33452","headword_ar":"مُفْرَدٌ","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodN","text_ar":"فَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", second quarter. ―         -b2-  [Hence, as a conventional term,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single, simple, word"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vocable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an expression of which a portion does not denote a portion of its meaning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforadaAtN","text_ar":"مُفْرَدَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Singular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as distinguished from dual and plural. ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforaAdaAtu AlT~ib~i","text_ar":"مُفْرَادَاتُ الطِّبِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The simples of medicine; medicinal simples."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforadN","text_ar":"مُفْرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wild bull."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L. [See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodN","text_ar":"فَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end.])"}],"source_refs":["KT"]},{"entry_id":"n33453","headword_ar":"مُفْرِدٌ","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A female, (S, L,) a pregnant female, (A,) or a ewe or she-goat, (M,) or a woman, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing forth one only:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, L, K:) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwHidN","text_ar":"مُوحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufi*~N","text_ar":"مُفِذٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L:) opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutoy^imN","text_ar":"مُتْيِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) [See its verb, 4.]"}],"source_refs":["S","L","A","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n33455","headword_ar":"مُفَرِّدٌ","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A rider"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no other with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or a rider"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having only his camel with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY lilomufar~idiyna","text_ar":"طُوبَى لِلْمُفَرِّدِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., (L,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good betide those who apply themselves to the study of practical religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the law, and withdraw from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rest of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind, and attend only to the observance of the commands and prohibitions"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, T, * L, K, TA:) and (K, TA) it is also said to mean (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those who are devoted to the commemoration of the praises of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or, as expl. by the Prophet himself,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those"},{"kind":"text","text":"men and women"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who commemorate the praises of God much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also, (K,) or, as Kt says in explaining the trad., (TA,) [and as his words are cited in the T,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those whose contemporaries in birth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the generation among which they were,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have perished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"died, while they themselves have remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commemorating the praises of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az holds the explanation of IAar to be more correct than this of Kt. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","L","K","TA"]}]}}